videoDescriptions.7228985669354343707: With the Coronation on Saturday, I had to try out King Charles & Camilla’s signature dish - the Coronation Quiche! Make yours this weekend too, here’s everything you need and the recipe 👇 1 x 20cm @Tower Housewares Precious plus non stick loose base sandwich tin (highly recommend this one as you won’t need to grease tin as the black diamond non stick coating is 7x stronger and it’s heavy duty). Remember my code SHAN20 will save you 20% You can make your own pastry or use 1 x 250g block of readymade shortcrust pastry  Filling 👇 125ml milk 175ml double cream 2 medium eggs 1 tablespoon chopped fresh tarragon Salt and pepper 100g grated cheddar cheese 180g cooked spinach, lightly chopped 60g cooked broad beans or soya beans 1. Lightly flour the work surface and roll out the pastry to a circle a little larger than the top of the tin and approximately 5mm thick. 2. Line the tin with the pastry, taking care not to have any holes or the mixture could leak. Cover and rest for a further 30 minutes in the fridge. 3. Preheat the oven to 190C. 4. Line the pastry case with greaseproof paper, add baking beans and bake blind for 15 minutes, before removing the greaseproof paper and baking beans. 5. Reduce the oven temperature to 160C. 6. Beat together the milk, cream, eggs, herbs and seasoning. 7. Scatter half of the grated cheese in the blind-baked base, top with the chopped spinach and beans and herbs, then pour over the liquid mixture. 8. If required gently give the mixture a delicate stir to ensure the filling is evenly dispersed but be careful not to damage the pastry case. 9. Sprinkle over the remaining cheese. videoDescriptions.7191531540717800710: Replying to @Mysterious Introvert AIRFRYER RICE CHALLENGE!! Can you cook rice in an airfryer - YES!! (Vizion dual basket airfryer link in bio) It’s Chinese New Year and I cooked egg fried rice, my fave! This was my first time cooking rice in an airfryer 💪 VERDICT - I wouldn’t have thought of cooking rice in the airfryer and it did take longer than traditional methods but it cook it! 👏 The airfryer can do it all! RECIPE  - One cup of washed rice with 2 cups of kettle boiled water, important not to use cold water as you would traditionally - helps speed the process up. - I used my own setting; 200 degrees for 30mins  - After 15 minutes I did add more water, and added a bit too much so if adding extra, be careful and pour little bit at a time - After rice started softening, I covered the basket with foil  - Scramble 4 eggs in the other basket - Once rice is cooked, fluff with a fork, add soy sauce, teriyaki sauce, chopped spring onions and the eggs and mix. Feel free to add salt and pepper to taste - Cook for a further 5 mins and serve  It tasted AMAZING! videoDescriptions.7465422493373697312: Be willing to give yourself the very best. Don’t let that pleasure be solely reserved for other people. Figure out a standard that you like, a level of excellence that feels good to you, and maintain that where you can in small ways on a daily basis. Some examples for me are, always making sure I’m eating of nice plates (no chips, and no reserving the extra nice plates for guests), I also make sure I look as put together as I can at home and have flowers and pretty things for me to look at in my space too-even when there are no guests! I don’t reserve the enjoyable things for only when I have other people around. I treat myself to nice holidays, dinners and experiences even if there is someone in my life that can give me the same. This can vary from person to person, and I’m by no means setting a rule and a standard for you but I hope whatever it looks like in your world, you give yourself the very best because you have the agency to do so.  Love, Marbie #selflovejourney #selflovetips #growthmindset #thatgirlroutine #thatgirlaesthetic

videoDescriptions.7423076842824944929: It’s okay for you to grieve out loud, for as long as you need to. At several points I’ve found myself policing myself around grief based on the unspoken rules around me. “Don’t cry”…or “she wouldn’t want you to be sad”…  Although well intended, sometimes the things we say to try and comfort those who are grieving can often act as a call to stifle those feelings.  Allow yourself, and others, to just sit with particular emotions sometimes. You don’t need to even provide any specific words of comfort if you don’t have any, just being with them in that space is enough.  Love, Marbie #griefjourney #griefquotes #lifelessonslearned #selfgrowthjourney #emotions #griefandloss

videoDescriptions.7411586419476401440: AD It's time to host like the French using @Boursinuk ! The Garlic & Herb flavour was the perfect addition to this one pan Orzo and it's such a great dish for hosting with loved ones. This recipe is incredibly simple but it packs a whole lot of flavour in there. Check out the full recipe using the link in my bio! Recipe: Name: One Pan Orzo with Boursin Garlic & Herbs Ingredients: 1x Boursin Garlic & Herbs Mirepoix (1 carrot, 1 celery stalk, 1 large shallot - chopped finely) 1x Chicken Stock Pot 1 cup of Pancetta Green seasoning (or finely chopped parsley, spring onions and shallots) 2 cups of Orzo 2 cups of white wine 1 tbsp of honey 2 cups of water Shallots, Asparagus and Courgettes cut into chunks Cherry tomatoes Extra Virgin Olive Oil Unsalted Butter Method: 1. Heat a pan with some Extra Virgin Olive Oil and unsalted butter, then sautee the mirepoix in this mixture for 5 minutes on medium heat 2.Add the stock pot, green seasoning and pancetta then stir until combined 3.Add the orzo to the pan, stir to combine, then add the wine and stir. 4.Season with some salt, black pepper and add hot water. Cover and leave to cook on a low heat for 20 minutes. 5. Sautee your shallots, asparagus, courgettes and cherry tomatoes in a separate pan. 6. Once cooked but still firm, add the veg to the orzo and stir to combine. 7. Turn off the heat, then immediately add the Boursin cheese and stir until well combined. 8. Serve and enjoy! #summerentertaining #dinnerparty #frenchdinnerparty #dinnerideas #orzo #orzorecipe #boursin

videoDescriptions.7397889740927700256: Always assess your motivations for doing things. You can be in pursuit of the most noble goals but with the wrong intentions and it will always catch up with you in the end. Don’t get sucked into the trap of trying to do anything to prove to someone that they were wrong about you. Half the time they actually aren’t even thinking about you. videoDescriptions.7208936042135571754: The truth is.. I’ve hated this fridge for the 7 years since we’ve had this house 🥲. Side-by-side fridges are my least favorite fridge layout, because both the freezer and the fridge compartments are extremely narrow, yet deep. Thus, everything gets lost in the Narnia depths in the back of the fridge. 😭 Because of my hatred for this fridge, I refused to buy the nicer organizers which would (and have) ultimately made my life easier. I probably would have saved a ton of money because food always got lost and went bad.  Recently, I decided to change my outlook, because this fridge has been good to us and she still (mostly) works fine.  I measured all of the areas meticulously and even made a written diagram of how I would store everything. Then I set out to find the right organizers to fit the dimensions and make the best use of the space. These are the results of that effort.  I’m so happy with how everything turned out! Now I that I can see what we have and everything has a specific location, I won’t have strawberry containers lost in the Narnia realm of my fridge 😅 I only wish I’d done this years ago!  As a mama, I’m all about making my life easier and I won’t be shamed about that. I do most of the shopping and food prep in our family and this will make my life so much easier and was worth the expense. So if this is not for you, that’s fine, but my mind will not be swayed.  People shouldn’t feel shamed for curating their homes in a way that makes them happy and brings them more peace.  #asmr #restock #reset  #amazonfinds #kitchen #kitchenorganization #fridgeorganization #fridgegoals #organization #organizedhome #fridgerestock

videoDescriptions.7455776206789561646: The right way to deep clean your kitchen: Part 1 (instructions below)  1) Top-Down Method: Clean from the top and work your way down to the floors. This method is the most efficient and ensures you won’t miss any surface areas.  2) Start by dusting and cleaning all upper cabinets, the oven hood and light fixtures.  3) Next, clean the backsplash, windows, and countertops. 4) Move to the stove top, remove any burner parts and let them soak in hot water (I like to use dishwasher pods as they fight grease and grime). Spray down the stovetop with Dawn power wash, and then spray the inside of the stove with a degreaser. Let both cleaners sit and breakdown grease while you turn to cleaning the stovetop burners. Once complete, finish scrubbing the stove (inside and out) and return the stovetop items to their place.  5) Next, clean the fridge, dishwasher, microwave and any small appliances (not shown here, but will be shown in part 2).  6) Disinfect the sink, sink faucet nozzle and garbage disposal.  7) Finally mop floors (not shown here, but will be shown in part 2).  Was that helpful? Do we like longer captions with explanations? videoDescriptions.7383784091671432490: Almost lost an eyelash in the batter 🫠 Recipe ⬇️ Ingredients  1 cup cornmeal 1 cup all-purpose flour 1/3 cup brown sugar 3 teaspoon baking powder 1 teaspoon salt 2 large eggs 2/3 cup buttermilk 2 cup blueberries 3 tablespoon of oil for pan Instructions •Preheat oven to 450 degrees F •Spread 3 tablespoon of oil in a round cast iron skillet. •Mix cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. •Beat eggs and buttermilk. •Add egg mixture to flour mixture and mix until just combined. •Fold in blueberries until just combined. Try not to over mix. •Bake at 450 for 10 minutes and then reduce heat to 375 and bake for 10 more minutes or until brown. #cornbread #blueberrycornbread #easyrecipe #soulfood #foodie #momsoftiktok #comfortfood #howto #southerngirl #brunchideas #foryou #fyp #easyrecipes

videoDescriptions.7379748017076849963: Women in STEM 🤩 I’ve been wearing makeup for 25 years and this is by far the best method I have found to get my brushes fully cleaned and dried quickly. These brushes are over a year old but look new 😍   Method & Rationale:  1. You will need 2 large jars for the two step soaking process. 2. You will also need: blue Dawn dish soap (gentle yet effective); Dial antibacterial soap (for eliminating the bacteria that might be linering in hour brushes); micellar water (breaking down the makeup) and a power drill that can be adusted for different drill bits. 3) First add micellar water and water to one jar; and dawn, water and dial to another jar. I soak the brushes for about 5 min in micellar water. Then I switch them to soap mixture.  4) Clean each brush using the power drill. And spin to rinse and dry. Let them dry on a towel or cooling rack.  #asmr #asmrsounds  #cleaningmakeupbrushes #cleaningmakeupbrushesasmr  #makeup #makeupbrushescleaning #aesthetic #satisfying #viral #clean #CleanTok #cleanwithme

videoDescriptions.7338510063197326638: Puff Pastry Bunnies 🤩 How to make them: Ingredients: • 2 puff pastry sheets thawed to room temperature) I prefer the Pepperidge Farm brand • Nutella (I warm it up for about 30 seconds in the microwave to make it easier to spread) • 1 tbs of melted butter and 1 egg for an egg wash (optional)  • Powdered sugar  1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees  2. Roll out pastry dough and spread the Nutella on the dough  3. Lay another pastry sheet on top  4. Cut bunny shapes with a cookie cuter 5. Brush on the egg/butter wash  6. Cook for about 10-12 minutes or until browned on top but watch it for burnjng. Let cool and then sprinkle on the powdered sugar  #Easterbunny #puffpastry #nutella #trending #foryou #pastry #easyrecipe #momlife

videoDescriptions.7464646956770397483: Plant shopping takes STRATEGY! 🪴📝🛍️ —— Here is how you can make the most out of your plant shopping trips: 1. Go in with a BUDGET! Make sure your account won’t be mad at you after this trip 2. KNOW YOURSELF! Be mindful of your space & ability to maintain constant plant care! Should you opt for a plant that thrives in medium to low light & requires little to no care OR are you a plant micromanager like me and prefer to buy plants that need more attention? 3. Try your hand at the 2in pixie plants! If you are ever unsure of your ability to care for a specific plant, try the small pots!  4. GOOGLE IS YOUR FRIEND. Pick up your phone and Google the care requirements on your selected plant. I promise - I still do this as a plant momma to over 400 plants 5. INSPECT THAT PLANT! Make sure you take time to really look at your selected plant ensuring that it’s pest free! PRO-TIP: Always purchase the plant with active new growth. That is a good sign that the plant has a healthy root system and will have less trouble accumulating to your home. Happy Plant Shopping y’all! @Pike Nurseries  #plantmom #plantshopping #plantlover #plantcollection #plantsmakepeoplehappy

videoDescriptions.7429736862169959726: Did you know? POCs are statistically less likely to own indoor plants! 🌱 But why is that? videoDescriptions.7428620291267513646: Adding more Pl(art) to my jungle paradise with @Najai 🪴🖼️🎨 ——— “Family Tree” is a visual exploration of sensuality, nature, and feminine energy, born from a collaboration between myself, a plant enthusiast and educator, and my sister, an erotic surrealistic artist. This series weaves together our mutual love for eroticism, women, and the botanical world, highlighting the intricate connection between the human body and the natural forms of plants.   Each piece centers around one of five plant families—Monstera, Philodendrons, Begonias, Anthurium, and Alocasia—chosen for their organic beauty, symbolism, and rich textures. The plants become metaphors for growth, resilience, and the nurturing qualities found in both nature and femininity. Find these AND MORE at www.paigetailyn.com #plantart #plantsmakepeoplehappy #plantmom #plantlover #plantcollection #creatorsearchinsights

videoDescriptions.7423800555744693550: You have mold, friend 😞🪴 It’s all good though - we’re going to get you right :) —— A question that I get pretty often is “Paige, what is this white stuff growing on the top of my potting soil?” Well, my friends, that is mold. Don’t be alarmed! Plants are living organisms, and it is normal to expect mold. Now, we have to remedy this. @nakedrootplanters are planters that allow your plan to breathe! These help with providing your plants adequate drainage and aeration. Pair the planter with a well draining soil and you’re all set. @solsoils has the perfect house plant chunky mix. If you’re in a hurry, feel free to scrape the mold off of the top of the soil and sprinkle cinnamon on top as cinnamon is the perfect fungicide. #plantsmakepeoplehappy #plantmom #plantlover #plantcollection #creatorsearchinsights #plantmold

videoDescriptions.7421200143711571243: I wish I had someone to keep it real with me when I started my plant journey! 🪴 —— My green thumb may look different than yours. Here are some plants that (in my opinion) are worth purchasing and leaving at the store.  1. Sygoniums have proven to be one of the easier plants to care for my collection. They come in a variety of colors and shapes and just don’t give me a headache. 2. Hoyas are boring. 3. You can absolutely never go wrong with incorporating any type of Pothos in your collect. SO EASY. Hard to unalive. 4. I hate Fiddle Leaf Figs 5. THE QUEEN. MONSTERA DELICIOSA! Looks expensive, but it’s easy to care for.  6. Calatheas and Marantas are like living in H3ll 7. Allocations are beautiful, but they are absolutely spider mite magnets. 8. Chinese evergreens are some of the toughest in the game! if you are entry-level and you want some thing that is absolutely low maintenance. This is the one. 9. My beef with the philodendron summer glory is that it is a crawling plant and it is not very friendly to apartment livers. 10. The philodendron bill has one of the most stunning shapes of leaves. The downside is that they grow incredibly slow! They are easy to care for tho! 11.  if you want some thing that’s velvety and sexy and soft. Definitely get yourself a philodendron Micans! So cute and demure  #plan#plantsmakepeoplehappyn#plantmomn#plantlovern#plantcollectiona#creatorsearchinsights

videoDescriptions.7410439628307647790: Codiaeum Variegatum ‘Mammy’?! What do you mean? 👀🤔🪴 —— SOUND OFF🗣️ Should the name of this plant stay as is? Let me know in the comments —— I barely scratched the surface with this one! croutons were brought to the US in 1886 by R.R McCormick, a conservative journalist, to decorate his Florida home in which he named “ Cotton Cottage”.  📝🪴 CARE FACTS: - ☀️ these plants prefer very, very bright light! This is how they keep their beautiful variegation. - 💦 keep your Croton moist, but not wet! They do not like to dry out - 🌞❄️ if you keep your crouton outside during the winter or near a window during the cold months, they will most certainly drop all of their leaves! So keep them warm and they will be happy.  #p#plantsoftiktokp#plantcollectionp#planthistoryp#plantmomc#crotonp#plantsmakepeoplehappyp#plantlover

videoDescriptions.7398564710435654954: STOP POTTING YOUR PLANTS DIRECTLY INTO DECORATIVE PLANTERS! 🗣️🪴 —- Using a nursery pot inside a decorative planter has several advantages: 1. Better Drainage:Nursery pots typically have more drainage holes, preventing water from accumulating at the bottom and reducing the risk of root rot.     2. Easier Watering: You can remove the nursery pot to water your plant, allowing excess water to drain thoroughly before placing it back in the decorative planter. 3. Plant Health Monitoring: It’s easier to check the root health and soil moisture levels in a nursery pot, ensuring your plant's needs are met. 4. Convenient Repotting: When the plant outgrows its pot, repotting is simpler because you can easily lift the nursery pot out without disturbing the roots. 5. Flexibility: If you want to change the look of your space, you can switch out the decorative planter without disturbing the plant.    6. Prevents Damage: Using a nursery pot protects your decorative planter from soil and water stains, keeping it in better condition. #plantmom #plantlover #plantsoftiktok #plantsmakepeoplehappy
videoDescriptions.7397808363196697898: It happens to the best of us 🤷🏾‍♀️🪴 —- I promise it doesn’t mean that your green thumbs don’t check out! Let me tell you why this happens: 	1.	🖼️Environmental Change: They experience a drastic change in light, humidity, and temperature compared to their previous environment. 	2.	😬🪴Handling Stress: Moving plants can cause physical damage to roots and leaves, leading to stress and shock. 	3.	💦Watering Differences: The watering schedule and water quality may differ, affecting the plant’s hydration and health. 	4.	💨Air Quality: The new location might have different air quality, including variations in ventilation and air circulation. 	5.	Soil and Pot Change: If repotted immediately, the plant has to adapt to new soil conditions and pot size, which can be stressful. 	6.	🏡Microclimate Adjustment: Plants need time to adjust to the unique microclimate of your home, which includes factors like drafts, indoor heating or cooling, and other ambient conditions. #plantmom #plantlover #plantsoftiktok #plantsmakepeoplehappy
videoDescriptions.7397072625228549422: 🫣🤍🪴 I cannot believe I was able to get my hands on one of these! —- When I saw this variegated Alocasia Dragon Scale on @Canopy Plant Co website I had to cop!   Here is my care plan: 1. **Light**: Bright, indirect light. Avoid direct sunlight which can scorch the leaves. 2. **Water**: Keep the soil consistently moist but not waterlogged. Water when the top inch of soil feels dry. 3. **Humidity**: High humidity is essential. Aim for 60-80%.  4. ** Soil**: Use a well-draining, airy soil mix rich in organic matter. A mix of peat, perlite, and orchid bark works well. 5. **Fertilizer**: Feed monthly during the growing season (spring and summer) with a balanced, diluted liquid fertilizer. 5. **Pests**: Watch out for pests like spider mites, aphids, and mealybugs. Treat infestations promptly with insecticidal soap or neem oil. Keep an eye on your Alocasia Dragon Scale for any signs of distress and adjust care as needed. Don’t forget to grab your @@Instant Plant Foodfor 20% using code “BLOSSOMEFFECT” at checkout  ##plantmom##plantlover##plantsoftiktok##plantsmakepeoplehappy##alocasiadragonscale

videoDescriptions.7371486800050736426: Let's talk about Dieffenbachias pretty plants, but such a dark history. 🪴 ——- Dieffenbachias were reportedly used to harm slaves. The plant contains calcium oxalate crystals that can cause intense irritation and swelling of the mouth, throat, and digestive tract if ingested. Historical accounts suggest that slave owners used the plant's toxic properties as a form of punishment. Forced ingestion of the plant would cause severe pain and swelling, rendering the person temporarily unable to speak, hence the name "dumb cane." This practice highlights the brutal measures some slave owners used to control and punish enslaved people. #plantmom #plantlover #plantsoftiktok #planthistory #diffenbachia

videoDescriptions.7353660993798540590: Petty Paige here to tell ya’ to be mindful of the pots you choose to plant in 🌱🪴 ——— We all want our plants to look pretty with a cute decorative pot, but I challenge you to keep in mind how you are potting your plants.   My plants are potted in CLEAR nursery pots and then placed into a decorative planter. The clear pots help me keep an eye on the plants’ roots and identify if it needs a repot.  If you choose to pot your plants in terra cotta please mindful of salt buildup - because terra cotta pots allow water to evaporate through the sides, any salts or minerals in the water can be left behind on the surface of the pot. Over time, this can lead to a buildup of salts that may be harmful to your plants. Regularly flushing the pots with water or occasionally soaking them in a vinegar solution can help mitigate this issue. #plantmom #newplants #plantlover #plantmakespeoplehappy

videoDescriptions.7351424731515538731: Tired of your cutting rotting? Trust, We’ve all been there before. 🫠🪴 ————— 📝🪴 Let’s talk about WHY a root growth accelerator will help:  @Market Botany Prop Drops, A root growth accelerator, can help avoid rot by promoting healthy root development, which in turn improves the plant's ability to efficiently absorb water and nutrients from the soil. Strong, well-developed roots are better equipped to handle excess moisture and prevent waterlogging, which is a common cause of root rot. Additionally, Prop Drops contain beneficial microbes that can enhance soil structure and create a more hospitable environment for roots, further reducing the risk of root rot by improving drainage and aeration. Overall, by enhancing root health, prop dropscan contribute to the plant's resilience against conditions conducive to root rot. Would you give this a trg? #plantmom #plantlover #plantmakespeoplehappy #propagation

videoDescriptions.7339572361068596526: WE GOT PLANTS AT THE HOUSE 🪴🏠 Let’s make a prop box! ——— HERE IS WHY I DIDN’T CUT THE LEAVES OFF: I personally have had greater success rate when I left the leaves on. I do not like to do wet stick propagations, because every time I do them, I encounter rot. When you create your prop box, feel free to try out both. In fact, it is encouraged for plant parents to cut off their leaves to direct the plant's energy towards root development instead of maintaining foliage. It also minimizes the risk of fungal diseases and promotes a more balanced growth between roots and shoots, increasing the chances of successful propagation.  #plantmom  #plants #plantsmakepeoplehappy #plantlover #propbox
videoDescriptions.7339194482665000234: 🪴 let’s talk about the magnificent Monstera Deliciosa 🪴  The Monstera Deliciosa is a staple household plant! This plant is easy to care for, fast growing, and eye catching to any visitors. —- I have had Saige (the larger monstera pictured) for about three years now. When I purchased her she was in a 12 inch pot. She is now in a 20 inch pot. Here are some tips and tricks that I’ve learned to keep my Monstera Deliciosa happy: 1. SHE LIKES LIGHT. These plants are extremely adaptable but I recommend keeping your Monstera and bright, indirect light. 2. SHE LIKES WATER. Always keep in mind that Monstera’s are native to the jungle so she love a good glass of water. 3. SHE NEEDS FOOD. I mean, how else did you think that I got her this big? Big mama has got to eat.  4, HUMIDITY IS GREAT! While not necessary, I have found that my Monstera Deliciosa has done really well when I have had her near humidifier. 5. KEEP HER CLEAN! Take time at least once a week to wipe down her big, leafy foliage and she will thank you forever. Plants need clean leaves in order to properly photosynthesize.  #monsteradeliciosa #plantlover #plantmom

videoDescriptions.7459477597177515294: All of my jewelry was stolen from my checked bag👀 The story 👉🏻 A few months ago, all of my jewelry and my new Louis Vuitton were stolen from my checked bag while flying Delta. videoDescriptions.7458370301655551263: If you’re seeing this, it’s your sign to plan a vision board party with your girls.✨ Story time!👇🏻 Since 2019, my mom and I have started every year with a special tradition: making vision boards together. What began as a fun way to dream big turned into a powerful tool for manifesting our goals and shaping our lives.🤍 In 2019, we were just starting Everything Envy (Which was called The Clutter Bee then), pasting words like “success” and “growth” onto our boards. By the end of the year, so many of those dreams had come true, and we realized the magic wasn’t just in the pictures—it was in the clarity and focus it gave us. Each year since, we’ve made it a ritual to reflect, dream bigger, and align our goals. From growing our business to spending more time as a family, our boards have helped us stay inspired and intentional. This simple tradition has transformed our lives and brought us closer together. If you’ve never tried it, let this be your sign—dream big, reflect, and create space for the life you want. Who knows what you’ll manifest? #everythingenvy #visionboardparty #amazonhome #amazonfinds #amazonoffice #founditonamazon #creatorfavorites2025
